    "### Inspecting and cleaning the data\n",
    "\n",
    "Like most real-world datasets, it needed cleaning before it could say anything useful. I removed note rows that were not actual observations, fixed an inconsistent sensor name, converted the date column properly, and created time variables such as month, hour, and day of week. I also reshaped the data from a wide format into a long format so that each row represented a single sensor reading at a single time.\n",
    "\n",
    "That restructuring mattered. It made it much easier to compare movement patterns by sensor, by hour, and by weekday versus weekend."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "ca5e5866",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fix the typo in one sensor name\n",
    "ped.rename(columns={\"59 High Stret\": \"59 High Street\"}, inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove note rows such as \"Daylight Savings\"\n",
    "mask = ped['Date'].str.match(r'^\\d{4}', na=False) # Remove non-date rows (e.g. \"Daylight Savings\")\n",
    "ped = ped[mask].copy()"
   ]
  },
  {
